# Architecture & Data Model

Full detail: `.playbook/03_ARCHITECTURE.md`, `.playbook/09_DATA_MODEL.md`.

- Target shape: `data/*.json` (structured content) → `Render` namespace (in `assets/js/render.js` once it moves
  there in Milestone 4) → `index.html` (thin shell, `fetch()` + markup skeleton only).
- Renderer reads data; UI never owns data. Data and presentation stay separable at every layer.
- As of Milestone 3, content lives in `data/chapters.json` and `data/companies.json`, fetched at load. `index.html`
  must be served over HTTP for local testing (`fetch()` against `file://` is blocked by CORS — see `12_DECISIONS.md`
  DR-005); it is never double-clicked directly anymore.
- Every `data/*.json` file has a stable `id` per record, unknown fields explicitly `null`/`"Unknown"` (never
  omitted), and dates as ISO 8601 strings.
- No build step — no bundler/transpiler required; the site is still plain static files, just served rather than
  opened directly.
